label.value: Incomplete Right Bundle Branch Block by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a wide QRS complex with evidence of delayed conduction to the right ventricle, manifested by a widened initial portion of the QRS in V1 and V2, a widened S wave in V5, V6, I and aVL, and with QRS duration less than 120 ms. (CDISC)

label.value: Incomplete Bundle Branch Block by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of partially blocked cardiac electrical impulse conduction along the fibers of one or both bundle branches.

label.value: Exaggerated Placental Site Reaction

value.value: A non-neoplastic trophoblastic disorder characterized by the presence of an increased number of implantation-site intermediate trophoblasts infiltrating the endometrium and myometrium extensively. It is associated with pregnancy or abortion.

label.value: Multifocal Atrial Tachycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a supraventricular arrhythmia characterized by 3 or more distinct P wave morphologies with an isoelectric baseline, variable PR intervals and no predominant atrial rhythm. The ventricular rate is typically 100-150 beats per minute. (CDISC)

label.value: Junctional Rhythm by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a rhythm which originates in the AV junction and results in a normal heart rate. It is characterized by retrograde P waves which may be obscured by or may follow the QRS complexes. The QRS complexes may be narrow or may demonstrate aberration. (CDISC)

label.value: Sustained Ventricular Tachycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of ventricular tachycardia greater than 30 seconds in duration.

label.value: Non-Sustained Ventricular Tachycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of ventricular tachycardia less than 30 seconds in duration.

label.value: Ventricular Bigeminy by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a normal QRS followed by a premature ventricular contraction; a rhythmic pairing of normal and atypical beats originating in the ventricles in a 1-1 ratio.

label.value: Ventricular Trigeminy by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of two sinus beats followed by a premature ventricular complex for 3 or more consecutive cycles; a regularly irregular rhythm of normal and abnormal QRS complexes in a 2-1 ratio. (CDISC)

label.value: Ventricular Tachycardia Storm by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of multiple, temporally related, episodes of ventricular tachycardia or fibrillation, occurring three or more times in a 24 hour period.

label.value: Adenosine-Sensitive Ventricular Tachycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of tachycardia that is usually terminated by the administration of adenosine. Usually, it is a result of cAMP-mediated triggered activity and typically originates from the right ventricular outflow tract. This type of tachycardia occurs in patients with apparently normal hearts.

label.value: Verapamil-Sensitive Ventricular Tachycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a ventricular tachycardia that is terminated successfully with verapamil administration.

label.value: Brugada Syndrome Ventricular Arrhythmia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a pattern of right bundle branch block and ST-segment elevation within electrocardiogram leads V1-V3. This pattern emerges as a result of a defect in ion channel genes, resulting in atypical electrophysiological activity in the right ventricle and a propensity for malignant tachyarrhythmias.

label.value: Liver Epithelial Neoplasm

value.value: A benign or malignant epithelial neoplasm that affects the liver.

label.value: Short QT Syndrome

value.value: Ventricular tachyarrhythmias occurring in association with short QT syndrome.

label.value: Fascicular Tachycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of relatively short duration QRS complexes that originate from the region of the posterior fascicle (or occasionally the anterior fascicle) of the left bundle branch.

label.value: Bundle Branch Re-Entrant Ventricular Tachycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of ventricular tachycardia incorporating both bundle branches into the reentry circuit.

label.value: Idiopathic Right Bundle Branch Block by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of blocked cardiac electrical impulse conduction along the fibers of the right bundle branch that cannot be attributed to any cause.

label.value: Right Ventricular Outflow Tract Tachycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of ventricular tachycardia originating in the right ventricular outflow tract.

label.value: Acute Anterior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves with accompanying ST elevation in leads V3 and V4, which is suggestive of acute myocardial infarction of the anterior wall of the left ventricle. (CDISC)

label.value: Acute Inferior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves with accompanying ST elevation in leads III, aVF and often II, which is suggestive of acute myocardial infarction of the inferior wall of the left ventricle. (CDISC)

label.value: Acute Lateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves with accompanying ST elevation in leads V5, V6, I and aVL, which is suggestive of acute myocardial infarction of the lateral wall of the left ventricle. (CDISC)

label.value: Acute Posterior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding in leads V1 or V2 of an initial R wave duration greater than or equal to 40 ms, R wave greater than S wave, upright T wave, with accompanying ST elevation, which is suggestive of acute myocardial infarction of the posterior wall of the left ventricle. Evidence of inferior or lateral myocardial infarction is usually also present. (CDISC)

label.value: Anterior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V3 and V4, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the anterior wall of the left ventricle. (CDISC)

label.value: Liver Non-Epithelial Neoplasm

value.value: A benign or malignant non-epithelial neoplasm that affects the liver.

label.value: Inferior Wall Myocardial Infarction

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of an injury in leads corresponding to the anatomic region of the inferior wall of the heart.

label.value: [18F]-labeled Substance P Antagonist Receptor Quantifier

value.value: A radioconjugate consisting of the positron emitting radioisotope fluorine F 18 conjugated to the substance P antagonist receptor quantifier (SPA-RQ) used in radioimaging. [18F]-labeled substance P antagonist receptor quantifier is an antagonist of the neurokinin 1 (substance P) receptor (NK1R) and can function as a positron emission tomography (PET) imaging agent for detecting NK1R-expressing cells and tissues. NK1Rs are frequently expressed on the plasma membranes of tumor cells from glioblastoma and breast and pancreatic carcinomas.

label.value: Intra-Atrial Conduction Delay by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a delay in impulse propagation through the atria. This is characterized by broad P waves which are often biphasic in V1. (CDISC)

label.value: Junctional Bradycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a junctional rhythm with a heat rate which is abnormally low. (CDISC)

label.value: Lateral Wall Myocardial Infarction
Left Ventricular Hypertrophy by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding suggestive of a hypertrophied left ventricle, characterized by large QRS amplitudes and secondary findings of left atrial enlargement, left axis deviation, or typical pattern of ST depression and T wave inversion. (CDISC)

label.value: Right Ventricular Hypertrophy by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding suggestive of a hypertrophied right ventricle, characterized by large R wave amplitudes in the right precordial leads and secondary findings of right atrial enlargement, right axis deviation, and typical pattern of ST depression and T wave inversion in the right precordial leads. (CDISC)

label.value: Low QRS Voltage by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a QRS amplitude less than or equal to 0.5 mV in the limb leads or QRS amplitude less than or equal to 1 mV in the precordial leads. (CDISC)

label.value: Herpes Zoster

value.value: A common dermal and neurologic disorder caused by reactivation of the varicella-zoster virus that has remained dormant within dorsal root ganglia, often for decades, after the patient's initial exposure to the virus in the form of varicella (chickenpox). It is characterized by severe neuralgic pain along the distribution of the affected nerve and crops of clustered vesicles over the area.

label.value: Non Q Wave Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of ST and T wave abnormalities in the absence of pathologic Q waves, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction in one or more regions of the heart. (CDISC)

label.value: Posterior Wall Myocardial Infarction
Septal Myocardial Infarction
T Wave Abnormality by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a T wave which appears peaked, inverted, flattened or biphasic.

label.value: Ventricular Hypertrophy by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding suggestive of an enlarged cardiac ventricle.

label.value: T Wave Inversion by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of an inversion of the T wave from the expected axis.

label.value: T Wave Peaked by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding in which the T wave appears increased in amplitude and cresting at a point.

label.value: T Waves Biphasic by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a T wave with both positive and negative components. (CDISC)

label.value: T Waves Flat by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding in which the T wave appears decreased in amplitude.

label.value: U Waves by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a small hump following the T wave occurring during the final phase of Purkinje repolarization.

label.value: Distal Bile Duct Carcinoma

value.value: A carcinoma that arises from the common bile duct distal to the insertion of the cystic duct.

label.value: Wide QRS Tachycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of three or more consecutive wide QRS complexes of uncertain origin with a rate greater than a certain threshold (100 or 120 beats per minute are commonly used). (CDISC)

label.value: Varicella Zoster Virus

value.value: An icosahedral, enveloped virus containing a single molecule of linear double-stranded DNA of 125000 nucleotides that infects only humans. It is the causative agent of chickenpox and shingles.

label.value: Vectorcardiograph Corrected

value.value: This is a measurement of electric heart vectors whereby this type of measurement aims to create an orthonormal measurement of the electric cardiac vector.

label.value: Vectorcardiograph Uncorrected

value.value: A measurement of electric heart vectors whereby this type of measurement does not consider the distortions caused by the boundary and internal inhomogeneities of the body. These lead systems assure the direction of the spatial line connecting an electrode pair and yields the orientation of the corresponding lead vectors.

label.value: Q Axis Left Axis Deviation

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of the Q axis from -30 to -90 degrees.
